Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.38,0:00:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know there's an awesome\Ntreasure at the end of this sea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.61,0:00:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And whoever gets it can be King\Nof the Pirates! Isn't that exciting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.18,0:00:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unheard-of adventures are waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.39,0:00:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage! Let that shred of courage grow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.26,0:00:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught a glimpse of\Nthe tail end to the future
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.90,0:00:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The horizons everyone\Ndreamed of were separate at first
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.68,0:00:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now they can be seen\Nthrough a single telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.82,0:00:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bitter compass of destiny\Nis leading your heart astray
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.16,0:00:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so turn the wheel in the other direction!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.06,0:01:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.13,0:01:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toss aside your bonds and your past
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.37,0:01:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can surely smile despite that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.38,0:01:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tears shed trying to achieve\Nyour dreams aren't for naught
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.86,0:01:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Precious in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.26,0:01:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught a glimpse of\Nthe tail end to the future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.54,0:01:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another warrior has perished...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.31,0:01:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then there was that earthquake... Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.98,0:01:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the evil spirits!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.42,0:01:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--We're going to deal with you right now!\N--T-This wasn't the agreement! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.85,0:02:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Stop!\N--Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.00,0:02:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Seto! Move aside!\N--What's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.80,0:02:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Shandoran warriors\NI know and look up to...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.40,0:02:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...have much more pride than this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.54,0:02:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.14,0:02:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Free from the Spell!\NThe Great Warrior Sheds Tears!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.92,0:02:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this sun lowers in the\Nwest and sinks once again...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.19,0:02:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...your men's lives will be offered to the gods!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.60,0:02:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.81,0:02:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The earth certainly swallowed you skillfully!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.91,0:03:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Truly an act of god! The fact that\Nyou're alive is what's hardest to believe!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.50,0:03:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The entire ground?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.98,0:03:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare for the ceremony!\NTake every last sacrifice to the altar!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.18,0:03:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait a little longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.92,0:03:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The commodore'll be back!\NJust two more hours! No, one! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.99,0:03:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we have to be burned at the stake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.33,0:03:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun is setting. The ceremony\Nshould be starting soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.97,0:03:54.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How unsightly! Is this the wreck\Nof a man who defied the gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.41,0:03:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you so afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.48,0:03:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.78,0:04:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You tremble before intangible fears
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.58,0:04:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and give up people's lives\Nfor false consolation!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.75,0:04:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,False consolation?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.79,0:04:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your sacrifices are nothing\Nbut pointless deaths!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.43,0:04:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have lived this way for centuries now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.27,0:04:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't mean it's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.87,0:04:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence, outsider!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.14,0:04:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However great your gods may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.68,0:04:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,people's lives are even more precious!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.42,0:04:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take the sacrifices to the altar!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.72,0:04:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burn them at the stake and\Nsend them into the heavens!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Commodore!\N--We're gonna be set on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.00,0:04:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can send an innocent girl to her death...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.77,0:05:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and have no qualms about it,\Nso I doubt you'd understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.98,0:05:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What you're doing is less than human!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.62,0:05:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No qualms, you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.32,0:05:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The girl yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.99,0:05:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was my daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.83,0:05:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You would tell your own\Ndaughter to end her life?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.73,0:05:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you people who don't\Nunderstand how much power there is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.77,0:05:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the words our priests hear from the gods!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.84,0:05:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our village is commanded to obey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.84,0:05:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't beg for our children's lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.42,0:05:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's one size smaller... It must\Nbe the Kashi God's child!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.06,0:05:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gods' blood has come\Nto pass judgment on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.10,0:06:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Judgment, my ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.07,0:06:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sixty years ago, my own land\Nlost hundreds of thousands of lives
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.41,0:06:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the Kinetsu plague that\Nis ravaging your village now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.41,0:06:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, in recent years, there've been\Nabsolutely no deaths to this disease!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.72,0:06:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.99,0:06:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because we discovered a cure for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.19,0:06:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I'm holding in my right\Nhand is the bark of a Cona tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.39,0:06:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Conine I can extract from it is the cure!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.00,0:06:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I return with this, I can save the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.14,0:06:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know how many man-hours\Nhave been spent around the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.31,0:06:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and how many victims there have been?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.05,0:06:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you people are trampling\Nall over this great advancement!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.22,0:07:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I say your "ceremonies"\Nare insults to those people!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.16,0:07:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will I die in judgment, or in an accident?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.24,0:07:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will your village die by curse, or by disease?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.17,0:07:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you that afraid of gods?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.51,0:07:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do know when a man is\Nspeaking earnest words...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.59,0:07:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.76,0:07:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did I just kill?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.93,0:07:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--A snake.\N--No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.37,0:07:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just broke our\Ncommandments and killed a god!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.24,0:07:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you call it a snake, and our\Ndeadly curse a curable disease!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.95,0:08:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you really save my beloved village?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.52,0:08:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you save it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.56,0:08:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.80,0:09:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A snake!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.04,0:09:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.54,0:09:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Calgara! Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.38,0:09:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a shock! I didn't know\Nthat snake had a grandchild...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.18,0:09:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That snake"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.02,0:09:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A snake, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.32,0:09:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those two make no sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.29,0:09:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were trying to kill each\Nother until just recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.60,0:09:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, they're such good friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.03,0:09:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara is never very friendly\Nwith any of the villagers, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.70,0:10:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen him smile like that before...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.34,0:10:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.34,0:10:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We climb down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.45,0:10:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Climb down?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.09,0:10:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This ringing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.96,0:10:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Calgara! Where is this\Nbeautiful ringing coming from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.43,0:10:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me and you'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.51,0:11:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.48,0:11:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lost for words?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Shandora, a city of gold.\NWe are its survivors!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.89,0:11:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A city of gold...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.83,0:11:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like I'm dreaming!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.34,0:11:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Whoa! It's gold everywhere!\NIt's a city of treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.22,0:11:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.89,0:11:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.12,0:12:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Load your ship with all the treasure\Nyou can, aside from the gold bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.59,0:12:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto! Show them where the treasure is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.17,0:12:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Right!\N--Are you sure this is okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.60,0:12:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The villagers already agreed to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.24,0:12:17.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We owe you for saving our tribe\Nfrom that terrible disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.98,0:12:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.15,0:12:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so generous, Great Warrior!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.95,0:12:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But haven't your people been\Nprotecting the city all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.79,0:12:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We've protected the city...\Nbut not necessarily its treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.09,0:12:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be more specific...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.40,0:12:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...only this stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.74,0:12:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? Writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.08,0:12:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Writings of history.\NIt's known as a "Poneglyph."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.92,0:13:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't read it, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean your ancestors didn't write this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.89,0:13:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All we know for certain is\Nthat this city of Shandora
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.13,0:13:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,fought and fell trying to protect this stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.10,0:13:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must continue to protect it\Nwith that amount of resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.57,0:13:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As descendants, it is our\Nduty to protect the proof
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.04,0:13:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that our ancestors fought and survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.12,0:13:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We revere our ancestors as if they were gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.32,0:13:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I had no idea it was this\Ngiant, gold bell I had heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.53,0:13:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This bell's ringing has words to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.36,0:13:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Words?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.87,0:13:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that the spirits of our ancestors\Nwho were greeted by the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.80,0:13:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can return to this land at\Nany time without getting lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.78,0:14:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we continue to ring this bell,\Nas a way to say, "We are here!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.18,0:14:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its sound proclaims the\Nunquestionable glory Shandora once had,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.46,0:14:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and makes its existence\Nknown to the ends of the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.93,0:14:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will never run or hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.10,0:14:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we call this city's\Ngrand bell the "fire of Shandora."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.34,0:14:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That explains why it has\Nsuch a majestic sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.87,0:14:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Do you think so?!\N--Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.11,0:14:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This fire reached out to us\Nand helped us arrive here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.48,0:14:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard this bell in a storm where\Nit shouldn't have been audible...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.76,0:14:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You like this bell's sound, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.53,0:15:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to grow up to be like\Nthat other giant snake someday?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.97,0:15:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably not for a hundred more years!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.28,0:15:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Stay here as long as you like, Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.15,0:15:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the first guests here in\Nthe 400 years since Shandora fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.79,0:15:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to treat you with lavish hospitality!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.43,0:15:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love that! I do want to\Ncollect plants from the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.90,0:15:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I want to see this\Nplague all the way through.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.03,0:15:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore! Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.07,0:15:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, now. What's with the clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.97,0:15:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, look! An Eternal Pose!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.04,0:15:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a map, Commodore! A map!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.94,0:15:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We took these from intruders.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.78,0:15:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a map of this island?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.32,0:15:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. This skull shape is definitely this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.49,0:15:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name "Shandora"\Nmeans "the skull's right eye,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.09,0:15:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which refers to this city's location.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.86,0:16:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, take care! Be sure she gets lots of rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.10,0:16:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.11,0:16:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Come look, everyone!\NNoland's giving us some weird crops!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.11,0:16:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a greenhouse on our ship,\Nwith all kinds of plant samples.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.12,0:16:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave some seeds and sprouts\Nthat are suited for your soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.85,0:16:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that any good?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.36,0:16:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure is! It's also full of nutrients!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.05,0:17:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Let's work hard again today!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.92,0:17:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Work hard doing what?\NHaving a campfire party?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.67,0:17:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why would the doctor\Nand the others do this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.91,0:17:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief! Noland and the others are coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.55,0:18:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen! Do not speak of last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.29,0:18:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said they are going\Nto set sail in a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.66,0:18:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not do anything rash!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.13,0:18:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we can't understand\Neach other after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.66,0:18:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how good his\Nmedicine is, he's still a god-killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.47,0:18:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do they think they're great enough\Nto stomp all over our history?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.64,0:18:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Endure it! Suppress your feelings,\Nand quietly wait for them to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.68,0:18:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.32,0:18:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys! Is Calgara around?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.36,0:18:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is everyone acting so coldly\Nall of a sudden? Where's Calgara?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.30,0:18:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are outsiders!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.47,0:18:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara doesn't want to see you anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.97,0:19:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.25,0:19:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When are you gonna leave, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.85,0:19:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.95,0:19:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They suddenly seem to hate us now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.56,0:19:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hold on, you guys!\NYou can't just start acting like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.56,0:19:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.86,0:19:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's continue our work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.53,0:19:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still have some forest to inspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.24,0:19:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are, Calgara!\NNoland was looking for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.08,0:19:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I don't want to see his face anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.21,0:19:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I do, I think I might kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.99,0:19:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bell didn't ring today...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.56,0:19:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's the first time this's happened\Nin the month we've been here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.00,0:19:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.47,0:19:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be finished exploring\Nthe forest in two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.60,0:20:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.64,0:20:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the crew we set sail again in three days,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.51,0:20:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so now's their last chance to\Nenjoy solid ground for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.81,0:20:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore... To be honest, I wanna\Nget off this awkward island...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.22,0:20:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only after we've finished\Nour duties! Get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.26,0:20:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Live here, Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.16,0:20:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know! Why don't you\Nmake Mousse your wife?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.16,0:20:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.37,0:20:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a family back home, with kids\Nabout her age. I have to go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.90,0:20:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara doesn't want to see you anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.71,0:20:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When are you gonna leave, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.09,0:20:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're here, Calgara! Come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.23,0:21:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think this is too one-sided?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.16,0:21:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me why! I won't\Nunderstand unless you tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.77,0:21:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to set sail very soon!\NI don't want to part ways like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.02,0:21:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't show your face around me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.19,0:21:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want your wife to end up a widow?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.20,0:21:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.17,0:21:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're feeling lonely, talk to me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.68,0:21:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gaze at the heavens\Nas you wander about
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.78,0:21:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the moon,\Nyou keep your gaze constant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.66,0:22:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your deep reflection wanes\Nas you slowly disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.84,0:22:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay as you are, let those words guide you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.02,0:22:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dream, you travelers who spend\Ncountless nights drifting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.10,0:22:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you may not be able to go back
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.53,0:22:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you will surely start moving forward again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.31,0:22:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bell has lost all its meaning!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.75,0:23:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only did what satisfied me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.49,0:23:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If these were sacrifices\Nfor your "advancements,"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.16,0:23:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we should never have accepted you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.12,0:23:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're right to be angry.\NWe have no reason to be forgiven!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.63,0:23:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're returning to the Lvneel Kingdom!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.83,0:23:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.17,0:23:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Eternal Friends! The Vowed Bell\NEchoes Across the Mighty Seas!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.54,0:23:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
